{{Quote|Sometimes, the paths we're on, they wind around in ways we never would have expected. All you can do is keep moving forward, even on days when honestly, it all just kind of feels like shit.|Eleanor Bishop to [[Kate Bishop]]|Ronin (episode)}}
'''Eleanor Bishop''' is the former CEO of [[Bishop Security]] and the mother of [[Kate Bishop]]. Following the death of her husband, [[Derek Bishop|Derek]], a tough financial situation had forced Bishop to become an associate of [[Wilson Fisk]], cooperating to his operations in [[New York City]], what she had to keep a secret from her daughter. When Kate started investigating the [[Tracksuit Mafia]] together with [[Clint Barton]], Bishop hired [[Yelena Belova]] and put a bounty on Barton's head. Eventually, Bishop realized that her daughter might be endangered, so she made a decision to quit working for Fisk. Bishop's decision had made her the target of the Tracksuits and Fisk himself, but she was saved by Kate, before she was arrested for [[Assassination of Armand Duquesne III|murdering]] [[Armand Duquesne III]].

==Biography==
{{MD|Eleanor Bishop (Earth-199999)}}
===Early Life===
====Marrying Derek Bishop====
Eleanor married [[Derek Bishop]]. Together they had a daughter named [[Kate Bishop|Kate]] and lived in the luxurious [[Bishop Residence|penthouse]] in [[New York City]] Derek had inherited from his family.{{Ref|HE101}}

====[[Battle of New York]]====
[[File:Eleanor Bishop & Derek Bishop.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop and her [[Derek Bishop|husband]] argue]]
{{Quote|Kate! We have to get out of here!|Eleanor Bishop to [[Kate Bishop]]|Never Meet Your Heroes}}
On [[2012|May 4, 2012]], Bishop was arguing with her [[Derek Bishop|husband]] over selling their [[Bishop Residence|penthouse]] when they heard something clatter upstairs. Bishop told Derek that he was going to have to tell [[Kate Bishop|Kate]] and he went upstairs to her room. When he came back down, he told Bishop that Kate was okay and she was going to come down for lunch. As they were eating, Bishop showed Kate a cool trick to drop her food into her mouth, causing her to laugh. Bishop suggested Kate get the checkers board so they could play, to which Kate agreed.
[[File:Eleanor & Kate (May 4, 2012).png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop escapes from the [[Bishop Residence|penthouse]]]]
As Kate went upstairs to get the board, the aliens known as the [[Chitauri]] arrived in the city and flew past their house, blowing a hole in the side of the house. Bishop raced to find Kate and get her to safety. When she found her she was staring at the hole. Bishop swiftly scooped Kate up and ran down the stairs as they were crumbling. Kate repeatedly asked Bishop where her dad was until it was too late to save him.{{Ref|HE101}}

====Derek Bishop's Funeral====
[[File:Kate & Eleanor (2012).png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop attend her [[Derek Bishop|husband]]'s funeral]]
{{Quote|I need to protect us."<br>"[[Kate Bishop|Kate]], that's my job. Okay? Whatever you need, I'm here for you."<br>"I need a bow and arrow.|[[Kate Bishop]] and Eleanor Bishop|Never Meet Your Heroes}}
A few days later, Bishop and [[Kate Bishop|Kate]] attended [[Derek Bishop|Derek]]'s funeral and burial. Kate put her head on Bishop's shoulder and told her that she needed to protect them. Bishop told her that was not her job since she was the mother, but Kate ignored this and responded she needed a bow and arrow.{{Ref|HE101}}

====Repaying Debt====
[[File:Bishop and Fisk - Flashback.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop attends a meeting with [[Wilson Fisk]]]]
{{Quote|I know you've been dealing with my [[Derek Bishop|husband]]. But as I'm sure, you've heard, he's gone. So now you're dealing with me."<br>"I recognize you'd like to get down to business, I respect that.|Eleanor Bishop and [[Wilson Fisk]]|So This Is Christmas? - Deleted Scene}}
Following the death of her husband, Bishop learned that [[Derek Bishop|Derek]] was indebted to [[Wilson Fisk]], having borrowed money from the crime lord when the Bishops were struggling financially.{{Ref|HE106}} Fearing of Fisk's retaliation, Bishop met with him in a private place, informing him that Derek had passed away, so she would repay his husband's debts herself.
[[File:Eleanor - Flashback.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop agrees to work for [[Wilson Fisk]]]]
Fisk expressed his respect to Bishop's eagerness to get down to the business and extended his condolences for Derek's death to Bishop and her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]]. Fisk told Bishop that Derek's debt was rather significant, so she would have to work hard to deal with it, which Bishop understood. Bishop, however, stated that she would not be working for Fisk forever, to which he agreed, saying that she would be working until the debt was clear.{{Ref|HE106DS}}

====Engagement to Jack Duquesne====
{{Quote|It's fast, yes. But, you know, it's kind of nice being swept up in the romance of it.|Eleanor Bishop to [[Kate Bishop]]|Never Meet Your Heroes}}
In [[2018]], Bishop survived the [[Snap]].<ref name="EleanorSnap">[https://www.thewrap.com/hawkeye-did-kate-bishop-get-snapped-by-thanos/ ‘Hawkeye’: Did Kate Bishop Get Snapped by Thanos?]</ref> In [[2024]], Bishop began a romantic relationship to [[Jack Duquesne]], who had been a friend of the family for a while. The couple became engaged shortly after getting together, although Bishop did not tell her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]], who was away at college.{{Ref|HE101}}

===Charity Gala===
====Scolding Kate Bishop====
[[File:Kate Bishop and Eleanor Bishop.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop lectures her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]]]]
{{Quote|I know that young people think they're invincible and rich people think they're invincible and you've always been both. So take it from someone who hasn't, you're not.|Eleanor Bishop to [[Kate Bishop]]|Never Meet Your Heroes}}
In [[2024|December 2024]], Bishop received a call from the dean of her daughter's university, who informed her that Kate had destroyed [[Stane Tower]], which Bishop would have to pay for the reconstruction of. When Kate arrived home for the holidays, Bishop lectured her over the incident, and made her aware that she had already canceled all of her credit cards. Bishop warned her daughter that she is not invincible and she can and will get hurt someday, causing Kate to apologize. Bishop told her daughter that she could make it up to her by coming with her to a charity gala that she was attending that night.
[[File:Eleanor Bishop & Jacques Duquesne.png|{{AltFloat}}|[[Jack Duquesne|Duquesne]] helps Bishop with her coat]]
Kate noticed a number of swords around Bishop's home, asking what they were all doing there, as [[Jack Duquesne]] entered the room, holding a rose in his mouth. He was surprised by the presence of Kate, and Kate was surprised by the seemingly romantic relationship Bishop was exhibiting with Duquesne. Bishop told her daughter they would talk more at the gala, and left with Duquesne to go to the hotel.{{Ref|HE101}}

====Conversation with Kate Bishop====
[[File:Eleanor hugs Kate.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop hugs her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]]]]
{{Quote|Is there a part of you that could be happy for me?|Eleanor Bishop to [[Kate Bishop]]|Never Meet Your Heroes}}
Bishop and [[Jack Duquesne]] arrived at the charity gala and began speaking to other socialites at the party. Meanwhile, [[Kate Bishop|Kate]] learned of their engagement from [[Armand Duquesne III]] and went to confront her mother about it. Bishop apologized to Kate for not telling her first, but explained that she enjoyed being caught up in the romance. Kate then excused herself to go get air and Bishop asked her to come back and find her after.{{Ref|HE101}}

====Threatened by Armand Duquesne III====
[[File:Kate eavesdrops.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop argues with [[Armand Duquesne III]]]]
{{Quote|Is that [[Armand Duquesne III|guy]] threatening you?"<br>"I... Honestly, I have no idea.|[[Kate Bishop]] and Eleanor Bishop|Never Meet Your Heroes}}
Away from the party, Bishop engaged in an argument with [[Armand Duquesne III]], who was upset over his [[Jack Duquesne|nephew]]'s engagement to her. She dismissed Duquesne's accusations, but he warned her that he has powerful friends that she would not want to mess with, before walking off. As she walked away, she noticed [[Kate Bishop|Kate]] was eavesdropping. Bishop went back to the party, asking her daughter to join her as well, but she did not follow.{{Ref|HE101}}

====[[Robbery of the Black Market Auction]]====
[[File:Eleanor Bishop (Christmas Gala).png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop looking for her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]]]]
{{Quote|That was crazy. An explosion? Some kind of black market auction?|Eleanor Bishop to [[Kate Bishop]]|Hide and Seek}}
As Bishop was back at the party, an explosion in the cellar beneath the charity gala caused the lights to flicker in the hotel upstairs. The attendees of the party began evacuating the hotel, as Bishop tried to locate her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]] amidst the chaos.
[[File:Eleanor Bishop and Jack Duquesne.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop finds [[Jack Duquesne|Duquesne]] after the explosion]]
Bishop tried calling Kate's phone but her daughter did not answer. She was found by [[Jack Duquesne]], whom she asks if he knows where Kate was, but he did not know either.{{Ref|HE101}} Later in the night, Bishop spoke to Kate over the phone, who assured her that she was okay after the incident at the charity gala.{{Ref|HE102}}

====Murder of Armand Duquesne III====
{{Quote|I handled [[Armand Duquesne III|Armand]] like you asked.|Eleanor Bishop to [[Wilson Fisk]]|So This Is Christmas?}}
Bishop was ordered by [[Wilson Fisk]] to eliminate [[Armand Duquesne III]], as his suspicion of Bishop was growing and becoming dangerous. Bishop murdered her fiancée's uncle in his [[Duquesne Brownstone|home]], leaving his body on the floor, where it would be found [[Kate Bishop]] and Duquesne's maid.{{Ref|HE106}}{{Ref|HE102}}

===Averting Kate's Suspicions===
====Conversation at Bishop Security====
[[File:Eleanor Bishop's Office.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop and [[Jack Duquesne|Duquesne]] talk to [[Kate Bishop|Kate]]]]
{{Quote|What's this I hear about a [[Attack on Kate Bishop's Apartment|fire]] in your [[Kate Bishop's Apartment|apartment]] last night?"<br>"I can explain. Can we talk? Without the [[Jack Duquesne|interloper]]?|Eleanor Bishop and [[Kate Bishop]]|Hide and Seek}}
The next morning, Bishop went to her [[Bishop Security Headquarters|office]], accompanied by her [[Jack Duquesne|fiancé]]. [[Kate Bishop|Kate]] rushed into her office to talk to her, not realizing that Duquesne was there. Kate brought up the murder of [[Armand Duquesne III]] that took place the night prior, and began inquisitively asking Duquesne questions, but Bishop interrupted her.
[[File:Eleanor (Bishop Security HQ).png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop questions her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]]]]
Bishop changed the topic, asking her daughter about the strange clothes she was wearing and about the [[Attack on Kate Bishop's Apartment|fire]] that happened in her [[Kate Bishop's Apartment|apartment]] the night before. Kate refused to answer the questions in front of Duquesne. Bishop invited Kate to join her and Duquesne for dinner that night, which Kate hesitantly accepted under the condition that she could come up with the conversation topics.{{Ref|HE102}}

====Dinner and Fencing====
[[File:Kate, Jack & Eleanor.png|{{AltFloat}}|The Bishops and [[Jack Duquesne|Duquesne]] talk over dinner]]
{{Quote|[[Jack Duquesne|Jack]] is hiding something, Mom. Don't you think it's a little strange that the same night his [[Armand Duquesne III|uncle]] threatens you, he ends up [[Assassination of Armand Duquesne III|murdered]] by sword?|[[Kate Bishop]] to Eleanor Bishop|Hide and Seek}}
That night, Bishop and her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]] ate risotto with [[Jack Duquesne]], who had prepared the meal. Kate began talking about Duquesne's love of swords, and the two began talking about fencing.
[[File:Eleanor Bishop (12.20.24).png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop listening to the conversation]]
Bishop tried to change the conversation, but Duquesne insisted that his and Kate's common interest was good for their relationship. Kate asked Duquesne if he wanted to get out some fencing gear and go a few rounds, which Bishop tried to prevent to no avail, as Duquesne agreed and left to grab his gear.
[[File:Jack Duquesne the Swordsman.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop spectates the match]]
Bishop watched the two fence uneasily as she feared for her fiancé's safety, unaware he was a talented swordsman himself. Kate became increasingly aggressive with Duquesne as he continued to downplay his skill, attempting to stab him in the face after he took his helmet off to prove he was lying about his skill, and successfully getting him to parry her strike.
[[File:Eleanor and Kate.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop and her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]] argue]]
As Duquesne walked away to change out of his fencing gear, Kate tried to convince Bishop that Duquesne was suspicious, accusing him of being responsible for the murder of [[Armand Duquesne III]]. Bishop dismissed the accusation, telling Kate to stop worrying about it and to let the [[New York City Police Department|police]] handle the investigation. Kate tried to explain that the situation was bigger than just one murder, but was interrupted by Duquesne reentering the room.
[[File:Bishop Residence (December 2024).png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop and [[Jack Duquesne|Duquesne]] watch [[Kate Bishop|Kate]] walk off]]
Bishop dismissed Kate's concerns as anxieties relating to her uncertainties about the future, and tried to assure Kate that she had a certain future working at [[Bishop Security]] already laid out for her, although Kate expressed that she did not want the same future for herself that Bishop wanted. Bishop asked Kate to apologize to Duquesne, which she sarcastically did. When Duquesne tried to offer Kate a butterscotch, she grabbed her jacket and rushed out of the room, much to Bishop's confusion.{{Ref|HE102}}

====Meeting Hawkeye====
[[File:Eleanor Bishop meets Hawkeye.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop sees [[Hawkeye]]]]
{{Quote|I am letting you know that I cannot lose [[Kate Bishop|Kate]]. I've lost people before. I know in your line of work, you have, too.|Eleanor Bishop to [[Clint Barton]]|Partners, Am I Right?}}
When [[Kate Bishop|Kate]] tried to sneak into Bishop's penthouse with [[Clint Barton]] to access the [[Bishop Security]] database, Barton was met by [[Jack Duquesne]] who threatened the intruder with a [[Ronin's Retractable Sword|sword]]. Kate rushed to stop him, as Bishop also walked into the room, confused as to what was happening.
[[File:Eleanor Bishop & Jack Duquesne.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop talk to [[Clint Barton]] and [[Kate Bishop|Kate]]]]
The four of them sat down at the dining room table, where Bishop began questioning the duo as to what they were doing there. Kate tried explaining that her and Hawkeye were partners working on an [[Avengers]] mission, although Barton denied her claims, but eventually admitted that they were in fact working together at the moment. Kate tried to leave, but Bishop told her to stay, and asked that she could see Barton out.
[[File:Clint Barton & Eleanor Bishop.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop warns [[Clint Barton]]]]
As she walked Barton to the elevator, Bishop warned him that Kate was not a superhero, which Barton acknowledges that he already knew. When Barton joked that Kate was pretty good at the hero stuff, Bishop responded by saying that [[Natasha Romanoff]] was also good but she died anyway. Bishop told Barton that she could not lose Kate, telling him to leave her out of his mission, which he said he could not do but ensured that he would keep Kate safe.
[[File:Eleanor Bishop's Apartment.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop makes a phone call]]
After Barton left, Bishop made a phone call to [[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine]], but she did not pick up. Bishop left a voicemail telling her to call her back as soon as possible, as she had an urgent matter.{{Ref|HE104}} De Fontaine eventually got in contact with Bishop, who asked her to target Barton for assassination so that he wouldn't interfere with her business.{{Ref|BW}}

====Spending Time with Her Family====
[[File:Eleanor (December 2024).png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop talks to her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]]]]
{{Quote|Mom, I really need to talk to you about [[Jack Duquesne|Jack]]."<br>"Hey, could we... Um... Could we change the subject?|[[Kate Bishop]] and Eleanor Bishop|Partners, Am I Right?}}
Bishop sat in the living room with her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]] and [[Jack Duquesne|fiancé]], as Duquesne commented on how well Kate was keeping her composure around her [[Hawkeye|idol]]. After Duquesne walked out of the room, Kate once again tried to talk to Bishop about him, but Bishop once again changed the topic. She asked Kate to help her make some decisions about the Bishop holiday party, and tried to convince her as she tried to reject the proposal.
[[File:Jack & Eleanor dancing.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop and [[Jack Duquesne]] dance]]
Duquesne walked back in the room and, having heard the word "party," requested that there would be dancing. At Kate's comment that Bishop did not dance, Duquesne asked Bishop to dance with him, which she did while as he serenaded her. After the dance, the couple sat back down. When Duquesne misquoted an aphorism, the Bishops made fun of his tendency to recite aphorisms incorrectly. As the family laughed, Bishop expressed her appreciation for being able to be with her family.{{Ref|HE104}}

====Comforting Her Daughter====
[[File:Tearful Eleanor.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop cries while talking to her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]]]]
{{Quote|I know it's scary now, Kate. But this doesn't have to change who you are. It just means that what you do might look a little different than you dreamed of as a child. And preferably a little less reckless.|Eleanor Bishop to [[Kate Bishop]]|Ronin (episode)}}
At nighttime, Bishop witnessed her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]] coming back to her [[Bishop Residence|penthouse]] from a fight with minor wounds. She inquired as to whether [[Clint Barton]] was involved with them, to which Kate replied that he instead protected her and told her to stay away from him. Bishop embraced her daughter as she began to cry.
[[File:Hawkeye - Ronin.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop comforts her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]]]]
In Kate's childhood bedroom, Bishop tended to Kate's wounds. Bishop comforted her daughter as her dreams of becoming a superhero seemed to be coming to an end, and Bishop assured her she still had a good life laid out ahead for her. The two looked at Kate's first [[Kate Bishop's Bow and Quiver|bow]] hanging on the wall and reminisced about Kate's childhood. Kate admitted that she and Barton had been investigating the death of [[Armand Duquesne III]] and found incriminating evidence involving [[Jack Duquesne]] and a [[Sloan Limited|shell corporation]]. Bishop agreed to look into it, and told her daughter to go her things from her [[Kate Bishop's Apartment|apartment]] and come back home.{{Ref|HE105}}

====Jack Duquesne's Arrest====
[[File:Eleanor watches Jack's arrest.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop watches [[Jack Duquesne]]'s arrest]]
{{Quote|I looked into it, honey, and you were right.|Eleanor Bishop to [[Kate Bishop]]|Ronin (episode)}}
The next day, Bishop called the police on [[Jack Duquesne]] for his involvement with [[Sloan Limited]]. [[Kate Bishop|Kate]] arrived as two [[NYPD]] officers were arresting Duquesne. As Kate hugged her, Bishop told her that she confirmed her claims. Duquesne calmly insisted it was all a misunderstanding and that he had been framed, and as he was escorted by the police, he told Bishop that he understands her decision, Duquesne also claimed, optimistically, he would solve the issue and be back in time for her holiday party. Bishop blankly stared at her fiancé as he was escorted out of the penthouse.{{Ref|HE105}}

===Secret Unveiled===
====Meeting with Kingpin====
[[File:Eleanor Bishop & Wilson Fisk.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop greets [[Kingpin]]]]
{{Quote|My [[Kate Bishop|daughter]] is home now, and she's getting too close. And that's where I draw the line."<br>"There are no lines in this business."<br>"And that is why I have to leave this business.|Eleanor Bishop and [[Kingpin]]|So This Is Christmas?}}
During the morning of Christmas Eve, Bishop attending a meeting with [[Kingpin]]. Bishop explained to Kingpin that she felt that she had more than paid off her late [[Derek Bishop|husband]]'s debt to him, and that because of how close her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]] was becoming to the situation, she believed it was time to cut her ties with Fisk.
[[File:Wilson Fisk's Office.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop walks away from [[Kingpin]]]]
As Kingpin was responding negatively to Bishop's announcement, Bishop threatened Kingpin by telling him that she had kept copies of everything in a safe place as an insurance policy against him. Kingpin offered Bishop a minute to reconsider, which Bishop said she did not need and walked away. Unbeknownst to Bishop, she was being followed by [[Yelena Belova]], who recorded the meeting and sent the video to Kate.{{Ref|HE106}}

====Bishop Christmas Party====
[[File:Eleanor confronted by Kate.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop is confronted by [[Kate Bishop|Kate]]]]
{{Quote|Kate, do not go out there, it's too dangerous."<br>"You're the reason it's dangerous out there, Mom. Just stay put and stay out of this.|Eleanor Bishop and [[Kate Bishop]]|So This Is Christmas?}}
That night, Bishop arrived by limo to her Christmas party at the [[Rockefeller Center]]. Meanwhile, the [[Tracksuit Mafia]] was about to launch an attack on the party to take out Bishop, and [[Kate Bishop]] and her allies were searching for Bishop to protect her. She was quickly found by her daughter, who pulled her away to the pantry. Kate played the recording of Bishop's meeting with [[Kingpin]]. Bishop began to explain her actions to her daughter, but was interrupted by [[Jack Duquesne]], who walked into the room looking to speak to Bishop.

Bishop replied by simply told Kate not to worry about it because she had everything under control. Both of them heard gunshots coming from elsewhere in the building, and Kate left to go help [[Clint Barton]], telling Bishop and Duquesne to stay there. Bishop ignored her daughter's wishes and left in the opposite direction. Barton later tasked [[Orville]] with going to the pantry to find Bishop, but since she was gone, Barton and Kate asked their other LARPing allies to keep an eye out for her. [[Grills]] later located Bishop leaving the building out of a side door and alerted Kate.{{Ref|HE106}}

====Attacked by Kingpin====
[[File:Madame Bishop.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop cowers in fear at [[Kingpin]]]]
{{Quote|Don't leave, Eleanor. Come here. Let's talk.|[[Kingpin]] to Eleanor Bishop|So This Is Christmas?}}
Bishop was escorted back to her limo by her bodyguard, but when she entered the limo, she found the driver dead in his seat and witnessed her bodyguard be attacked and thrown over the vehicle. The door to the limo was aggressively ripped from the vehicle, and Bishop screamed and cowered in fear as [[Kingpin]] showed his face and attempted to grab her from the limo.
[[File:Eleanor unconscious.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop unconscious]]
[[Kate Bishop]] arrived and drew Kingpin's attention away from Bishop. While, Kingpin resisted all of Kate's attacks and knocked her to the ground, Bishop crawled up to the driver's seat of the limo and drove the vehicle at Kingpin, sending him flying through the wall of the store behind him, activating the limo's airbag and knocking Bishop unconscious for a few minutes.{{Ref|HE106}}

====Arrest====
[[File:Eleanor explanation.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop apologizes to her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]]]]
{{Quote|Is this what heroes do, arrest their mothers on Christmas?"<br>"I'm sorry. I love you, Mom.|Eleanor Bishop, and [[Kate Bishop]]|So This Is Christmas?}}
Bishop regained consciousness as her [[Kate Bishop|daughter]] went to check on her after her fight with [[Kingpin]]. Bishop apologized to Kate and promised her that everything was going to go back to normal, but Kate rejected the promise, unable to forgive her mother for killing [[Armand Duquesne III]], hiring [[Yelena Belova]] to kill [[Clint Barton]], and framing [[Jack Duquesne]] for her crimes.
[[File:Eleanor Bishop arrested.png|{{AltFloat}}|Bishop is arrested by the [[NYPD]]]]
As Bishop tried to reason with her daughter, [[NYPD]] Detectives [[Caudle]] and [[Rivera (NYPD)|Rivera]] arrived to arrest Bishop for her crimes, tipped off by Kate. Bishop tried to guilt-trip her daughter by asking her if superheroes arrest their mothers during holidays, but Kate apologized and told Bishop that she loved her as the police took her away.{{Ref|HE106}}

==Abilities==
{{Quote|Killing [[Armand Duquesne III|Armand]]? Hiring an [[Yelena Belova|assassin]] to kill [[Hawkeye|Clint]]? Framing your own [[Jack Duquesne|fiancé]]? That's an unfortunate arrangement?"<br>"Yes, sweetie. That's how the world works. I've protected you from it. You may not have known what was going on, but I did it for you. I know what it's like to have nothing. And you can't handle it.|[[Kate Bishop]] and Eleanor Bishop|So This Is Christmas?}}
*'''Master Tactician''': While working for [[Wilson Fisk]], Eleanor Bishop was able to arrange a shell company, [[Sloan Limited]], to act as the legal front for the [[Tracksuit Mafia]]. She named [[Jack Duquesne]] the CEO of the company as a failsafe in case anybody went looking into the organization. She also murdered [[Armand Duquesne III]] and managed to evade suspicion for almost a week, murdering him in a fashion that pointed suspicion at Jack Duquesne. When [[Kate Bishop]] began investigating the murder, the tactics worked as Kate believed Duquesne was the culprit. When Kate began asking questions, Bishop manipulated Kate by dismissing her accusations as a normal reaction to a soon-to-be stepfather and changing the topic, but when Kate began to line all of the evidence up, Bishop called the police on Duquesne to take the fall for everything. Her tactics might have worked longer if not for [[Yelena Belova]] tailing her and revealing Bishop as her employer to Kate.
*'''Expert Businessperson''': Bishop is an exceptional businesswoman and worked as the CEO of [[Bishop Security]].
*'''Physician''': Bishop has some basic physician skills, being able to treat some wounds that [[Kate Bishop]] acquired during her [[Infiltration into Maya Lopez's Apartment|fight]] with Yelena Belova and [[Maya Lopez]].

==Facilities==
*'''[[Bishop Residence]]''': Upon marrying into the Bishop family, Bishop moved into her [[Derek Bishop|husband]]'s penthouse that he had inherited from his family. In [[2012]], the [[Chitauri]] unintentionally destroyed the penthouse during the [[Battle of New York]], but it was repaired and Bishop moved back into it.
*'''[[Bishop Security Headquarters]]''': As the CEO of [[Bishop Security]], Bishop has an office at the headquarters that she runs.

